<!-- ====================================================================== 
   El calentamiento es un <exploration> (distinto a las otras actividades)
   Para RRRRR usar el estilo del calentamiento. Por ejemplo, usar 
   RRRRRR=observa con los "Observa y Pregúntate"
===========================================================================  -->
<exploration xml:id="warm-converNum-dividirEntre4" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Conversación numérica: Dividamos entre 4</title>

<statement>
  <p>Encuentra mentalmente el valor de cada expresión.</p>
  <ul>
    <li><p><m>12\div 4</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>24\div 4</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>60\div 4</m></p></li>
    <li><p><m>72\div 4</m></p></li>
  </ul>
</statement>

<solution>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>3: I just knew it. <m>3 \times 4 = 12</m></li>
      <li>6: 24 is twice 12, so the value of <m>24 \div 4</m> is twice that of <m>12 \div 4</m> or twice 3, which is 6.</li>
      <li><p>15:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>I knew that <m>4 \times 10</m> is 40 and <m>4 \times 5</m> is 20, so <m>4 \times 15</m> is 60.</li>
          <li>I knew that <m>20 \div 4</m> is 5 and 60 is 3 times 20, so <m>60 \div 4</m> is 3 times 5.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li><p>18:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><m>72=12+60</m>, so I added the values of <m>12 \div 4</m> and <m>60 \div 4</m>, which is <m>3 + 15</m>.</li>
          <li><m>4 \times 10 = 40</m>, <m>4 \times 8 =32</m>, <m>10+8=18</m>.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </solution>


